Privacy Policy

Last updated: March 2, 2026

This game ("the App") is developed by twelve52 LLC ("we", "us", or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how information is collected, used, and disclosed when you use the App.

Information We Collect The App itself does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information to our servers. We do not require account creation, and we do not ask for your name, email address, or any other personal details.

Game data such as your high score, settings, and progress are stored locally on your device using standard iOS storage and are never transmitted off your device.

Third-Party Services The App uses the following third-party services that may collect information:

Google AdMob — We display ads through Google AdMob. Google may collect and use data to serve personalized or non-personalized ads, including device identifiers, IP address, and usage data. You can review Google's privacy policy at policies.google.com/privacy.

Apple Game Center — If you choose to sign in to Game Center, Apple handles your Game Center profile and leaderboard data according to Apple's privacy policy at apple.com/privacy.

App Tracking Transparency — On iOS 14.5 and later, the App will request your permission before allowing third-party services to track your activity across other apps and websites. You can change this permission at any time in your device's Settings.

In-App Purchases The App offers an optional one-time purchase to remove ads. This transaction is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We do not receive or store any payment information.

Children's Privacy The App does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of 13. The App contains third-party advertising which may collect data as described above.

Data Retention Since we do not collect personal data, there is no personal data to retain. Local game data remains on your device until you delete the App.

Your Choices You can opt out of personalized advertising by adjusting your device settings under Settings > Privacy > Tracking. You can also purchase the remove-ads option within the App to eliminate all advertising.

Changes to This Policy We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page with an updated revision date.

Contact Us If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at general@twelve52cards.com
